<Layout title="Rules & Safety" description="Trail rules, safety guidelines, and etiquette for using the CRE Trails in Chesapeake Ranch Estates.">
  <section style="padding-top: var(--spacing-xl);">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Trail Rules & Safety</h1>
      <p class="text-center" style="font-size: 1.125rem; color: var(--color-text-light); max-width: 800px; margin: var(--spacing-md) auto var(--spacing-xl);">
        Please follow these guidelines to ensure a safe and enjoyable experience for all trail users
      </p>

      <div class="info-box warning" style="max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto var(--spacing-xl);">
        <h3>â° Hours of Operation</h3>
        <p style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600;">Dawn to Dusk - Year Round</p>
        <p>Trails are closed at night for safety and wildlife protection.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <div>
          <h2>Trail Rules</h2>
          
          <div class="card">
            <h3>âœ… Permitted Activities</h3>
            <ul style="margin-left: var(--spacing-lg); line-height: 2;">
              <li><strong>Hiking and walking</strong> - All skill levels welcome</li>
              <li><strong>Mountain biking</strong> - Ride responsibly</li>
              <li><strong>Dog walking</strong> - Dogs must be on leash</li>
              <li><strong>Nature observation</strong> - Enjoy the wildlife</li>
              <li><strong>Photography</strong> - Capture the beauty</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="card" style="margin-top: var(--spacing-md);">
            <h3>âŒ Prohibited Activities</h3>
            <ul style="margin-left: var(--spacing-lg); line-height: 2;">
              <li>Motorized vehicles (except mobility devices)</li>
              <li>Hunting or trapping</li>
              <li>Littering or dumping</li>
              <li>Damaging trees, plants, or trail markers</li>
              <li>Camping or fires</li>
              <li>Alcohol or illegal substances</li>
              <li>Loud music or disruptive behavior</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2>Safety Guidelines</h2>
          
          <div class="card">
            <h3>ğŸ¦º Personal Safety</h3>
            <ul style="margin-left: var(--spacing-lg); line-height: 2;">
              <li>Stay on marked trails</li>
              <li>Tell someone where you're going</li>
              <li>Carry a phone for emergencies</li>
              <li>Wear appropriate footwear</li>
              <li>Bring water, especially in warm weather</li>
              <li>Be aware of weather conditions</li>
              <li>Watch for roots, rocks, and uneven terrain</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="card" style="margin-top: var(--spacing-md);">
            <h3>ğŸš¨ In Case of Emergency</h3>
            <p><strong>Call 911</strong> for medical emergencies or injuries</p>
            <p style="margin-top: var(--spacing-sm);"><strong>Location:</strong> 424 Clubhouse Drive, Lusby, MD 20657</p>
            <p style="margin-top: var(--spacing-sm);">Trail markers can help emergency responders locate you. Note the color and any nearby landmarks.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-top: var(--spacing-2xl);">
        <h2>Trail Etiquette</h2>
        <p>Share the trail and be courteous to other users. Following these guidelines helps everyone enjoy the trails safely.</p>

        <div class="grid grid-3" style="margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-icon">ğŸ‘¥</div>
            <h3>Yield Appropriately</h3>
            <p><strong>Bikers yield to hikers</strong><br>Slow down and give plenty of space when passing.</p>
            <p style="margin-top: var(--spacing-sm);"><strong>Everyone yields to horses</strong><br>If equestrians are present, step aside and remain calm.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-icon">ğŸ”Š</div>
            <h3>Announce Your Presence</h3>
            <p>When approaching others from behind, give a friendly warning: "On your left!" or "Bike coming through!"</p>
            <p style="margin-top: var(--spacing-sm);">Keep conversations at a reasonable volume to preserve the peaceful atmosphere.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-icon">ğŸ‘£</div>
            <h3>Stay on Trail</h3>
            <p>Avoid creating shortcuts or new trails, which can cause erosion and damage vegetation.</p>
            <p style="margin-top: var(--spacing-sm);">Walk through puddles, not around them, to prevent trail widening.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-top: var(--spacing-2xl);">
        <h2>Dogs on Trails</h2>
        
        <div class="grid grid-2">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>ğŸ• Dog Requirements</h3>
            <ul style="margin-left: var(--spacing-lg); line-height: 2;">
              <li><strong>Leash required at all times</strong> - Maximum 6 feet</li>
              <li>Keep dogs under control</li>
              <li>Clean up after your dog - carry waste bags</li>
              <li>Dispose of waste in trash receptacles</li>
              <li>Keep dogs on trail, not in sensitive areas</li>
              <li>Ensure dogs are friendly with people and other dogs</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>ğŸ¾ Why Leashes Matter</h3>
            <p>Leash requirements protect wildlife, prevent conflicts with other trail users, and keep your dog safe from hazards.</p>
            <p style="margin-top: var(--spacing-sm);">Even well-trained dogs can be startled by wildlife or other dogs. A leash ensures you maintain control in unexpected situations.</p>
            <p style="margin-top: var(--spacing-sm);"><strong>Thank you for being a responsible dog owner!</strong></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-top: var(--spacing-2xl);">
        <h2>Leave No Trace Principles</h2>
        <p>Help us keep the trails beautiful for everyone by following Leave No Trace principles:</p>

        <div class="grid grid-3" style="margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>ğŸ—‘ï¸ Pack It Out</h3>
            <p>Carry out everything you bring in. This includes trash, food waste, and dog waste.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>ğŸŒ¿ Respect Nature</h3>
            <p>Don't pick flowers, disturb wildlife, or remove natural objects. Leave them for others to enjoy.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>ğŸ¤« Minimize Impact</h3>
            <p>Stay on trails, keep noise levels down, and leave the area better than you found it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-top: var(--spacing-2xl);">
        <h2>Seasonal Considerations</h2>
        
        <div class="grid grid-2">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>ğŸŒ Spring & Summer</h3>
            <ul style="margin-left: var(--spacing-lg); line-height: 2;">
              <li>Wear insect repellent for ticks and mosquitoes</li>
              <li>Check for ticks after your hike</li>
              <li>Stay hydrated in hot weather</li>
              <li>Watch for poison ivy (leaves of three, let it be)</li>
              <li>Trails may be muddy after rain</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>ğŸ‚ Fall & Winter</h3>
            <ul style="margin-left: var(--spacing-lg); line-height: 2;">
              <li>Wear bright colors during hunting season</li>
              <li>Trails may be slippery with wet leaves</li>
              <li>Dress in layers for changing temperatures</li>
              <li>Daylight hours are shorter - plan accordingly</li>
              <li>Ice and snow may make trails hazardous</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="info-box" style="margin-top: var(--spacing-2xl);">
        <h3>ğŸ“¢ Report Issues</h3>
        <p>If you notice trail damage, safety hazards, or rule violations, please contact the trails committee:</p>
        <p style="margin-top: var(--spacing-sm);">
          <strong>Phone:</strong> <a href="tel:443-975-4736">(443) 975-4736</a> | 
          <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:lydia@hotmail.com">lydia@hotmail.com</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: var(--spacing-2xl);">
        <p style="font-size: 1.125rem; color: var(--color-primary-dark); font-weight: 600;">
          Thank you for helping us keep CRE Trails safe and enjoyable for everyone!
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
